
Example SASL conf for Kafka.
In the subdir logstash you will find example conf for logstash.


0.
Install kafka into /opt/kafka_2.12-2.2.0/

1.
Copy files from this repo recursively into
kafka_2.12-2.2.0/

2.
Install logstash

3.
Copy logstash/etc/logstash/* recursively into /etc/logstash/

4.
Open a new shell. Start zookeeper using start-zookeeper.sh

5.
Open a new shell. Start Kafka using start-kafka.sh

6.
Open a new shell. Create topics using create-topic.sh

7.
Set ACL:s using set-acl.sh

8.
Open a new shell. Start a logstash producer using logstash/logstash-testproducer.sh
Current directory must be /usr/share/logstash/

9.
Open a new shell. Start a logstash consumer using logstash/logstash-testconsumer.sh
Current directory must be /usr/share/logstash/

10.
Write something on standard input (console) in the logstash-testproducer shell

11.
Check that the output appears on standard output (console) in the logstash-testconsumer shell


